## Summary

The compiled editorial report in `ReportDashboard` tries to read `scene.modeFeedback` from database scene objects, but editorial feedback is stored in React state (`modeFeedback`) in `App.jsx` and never persisted to scenes. The compiled report always shows "No editorial reviews run" for every scene.

**Fix:** Pass `modeFeedback` from App.jsx into ReportDashboard and use it when compiling the report.

<galaxy_edit_plan>
<edit_file path="proselab/src/App.jsx">
<search>
              <ReportDashboard 
                report={report} 
                text={text}
                chapters={chapters}
                scenes={scenes}
                activeProjectTitle={projects?.find(p => String(p.id) === String(selectedProjectId))?.title || "Active Manuscript"}
              />
</search>
<replace>
              <ReportDashboard 
                report={report} 
                text={text}
                chapters={chapters}
                scenes={scenes}
                modeFeedback={modeFeedback}
                selectedSceneId={selectedSceneId}
                activeProjectTitle={projects?.find(p => String(p.id) === String(selectedProjectId))?.title || "Active Manuscript"}

